reviews.review: With so many questions left unanswered from episode 8. JJ Abrams redeems the franchise and gives the fans a movie that allows them to let the Skywalker saga complete with satisfaction. This is no game of thrones final episode and could arguably be a favorite of many fans. At times this movie moves very fast and lacks the time to absorb the emotion of the scene, but that is to be expected when 49 years of Star Wars needs to come to a conclusion in 2.5 hours. Will be seeing again.

I don’t know if it was because Disney had some sort of talk with mrs Kennedy or something but this movie wasn’t that bad. JJ abrams obviously had his work cut out for him but if you go into this movie excepting that Rey will be over powered to the extreme and can and will beat the greatest sith ever. Hey at least in this movie she gets some training and actually struggles with the question of who she is and what that means. Which really help make this the best of the three. I hated the flash back of Luke and leia training but that’s ok. The three biggest comments I had to make was thank you for baby yoda introducing force healing before skywalker dying I mean rising came out. Also Disney next time call up jk Rowling and have her be in charge of keeping your ending secret because you guys really drop the ball. Lastly the skywalkers are dead her name is Rey palpatine not Rey skywalker. Let it show she isn’t afraid of her lineage anymore let her not lie to herself though the reveal was well done for those who didn’t know
I quite enjoyed it! JJ did a great job considering what he was left with after TLJ. It was great seeing the main cast together for once. Go see it!
if you did not like the last Jedi I think you're going to love it. if you liked the last Jedi you'll have a mixed reviews.
Bad Ass Movie!!! I do have some issues with it but overall, loved it!!! It definitely doesn’t seem like a complete trilogy though. TFA ROS .. odd one out is TLJ in my opinion.
Absolute rubbish props to JJ stepping into a bad situation but it was horrible ty Disney for killing starwars with an execution so many other stories could of been told and you went with garbage.
Not without its faults. But still a fun ride.
All in all the movie thrilled and provided the kind of fan service that I expected and loved from Star Wars

I loved the movie, found that it does a great job of closing out the Skywalkers Saga.
that said it does have a few issues but what movie doesn't. my biggest questions is about the emperor but asking the question would give away spoilers. 
I fell that it fixed issues and explained things from the last movies.  
as with anything it would have been a better if they had 1 writer for all 3 movies. 
that said i will be going to see the movie again.
The movie makes up for the shortcomings of the last Jedi.  My only regret coming out of this movie was that Abrams didn't get to direct Episode 8.
